The paper focuses on the message complexity of leader election in distributed networks, which is a topic related to distributed computing (cs.DC) and distributed systems (cs.DS). The study of message complexity also involves information theory (cs.IT) and network protocols (cs.NI). Additionally, the paper may be relevant to social networks and graph theory (cs.SI) due to its focus on network diameter.
